Definition.WordDefinition: Et cetera \Et` cet"e*ra\, ||Et caetera \Et` c[ae]t"e*ra\ . [L. et and + caetera other things.] Others of the like kind; and the rest; and so on; -- used to point out that other things which could be mentioned are to be understood. Usually abbreviated into etc. or &c. (&c.) --Shak. [1913 Webster]
etcetera n : additional unspecified odds and ends; more of the same; "his report was full of etceteras" adv : continuing in the same way [syn: {and so forth}, {and so on}, {etc.}]
